Title: Fall Quarter 2016 Week One
Description: Classes begin.Final week to register online or to register for internships and ILCs.Registration office open until 6 pm.Adding classes requires faculty approval.In-office only registration opens for tuition waivers: Evergreen employees, Washington state employees, 60+, and National Guard.

Title: Tuition Deadline
Description: Final day to drop classes for 100% refund.

Title: Fall Quarter 2016 Week Two
Description: Adding Classes incurs $50 late fee and requires faculty approval

Title: Fall Quarter 2016 Week Three
Description: Adding classes incurs $100 late fee and requires a petition and faculty approval.

Title: Fall Quarter 2016 Week Four
Description: Adding classes incurs $100 late fee and requires a petition and faculty approval.

Title: Fall Quarter 2016 Week Five
Description: Until October 25, adding classes incurs $100 late fee and requires a petition and faculty approval. October 25 is the final day for any registration in Fall 2016.

Title: Fall Graduation Academic Statement Due
Description: Seniors graduating Fall 2016 must turn in their final Academic Statement by this date.
